{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"LIVE-MATRIX IMPLEMENTED + RUN — GREEN (2026-07-09)\n\ntests/integration/test_reconcile_live_e2e.py: the 8 skip-scaffolds are replaced with real tests; `pytest -m live` = 12 passed / 0 failed / 0 skipped (JSON: reports/d01e-live-matrix.report.json; JUnit: reports/d01e-live-matrix.junit.xml — gitignored CI-artifact paths).\n\nEach scenario asserts ONE observable criterion against the REAL reconciler seam:\n- blast-radius (AC): classify.census([acting]*6+[noop]*5, total_bindings=11, max_acting_fraction=0.10)['breaker']['allowed'] is False; under-cap allowed True; census WITHOUT breaker inputs carries no 'breaker' key (no KeyError). Also check_blast_radius direct.\n- C1 (a713): outbound_differ._diff_fields(local!=baseline AND jira!=baseline) keeps local-wins (changed['description']=='local-edit') AND records ('C1-KEY-1','description') in conflict_sink; run_differs._emit_outbound_field_alerts -> alert_store.is_deduped('outbound-field-conflict:C1-KEY-1:description').\n- C3 (acd0): _diff_fields(issuetype differs) leaves issuetype OUT of the update AND records the drop; emit -> is_deduped('outbound-field-dropped:C3-KEY-1:issuetype'); second emit does NOT double-write (dedup == 1 line).\n- C4 (943f): _rate_limit_backoff — no-marker->None; 429 no-Retry-After->jittered in [2,3); Retry-After:7->7.0; Retry-After:999999->capped _MAX_BACKOFF_S(60). Full _run_acli loop: monkeypatched Popen returns 429 then success -> retries exactly once, sleeps a bounded jittered backoff (>=2.0), returns rc=0.\n- echo/idempotency: _diff_fields over equal (just-written) data -> {} (0 mutations); outbound_comments._decorate_outbound_comment carries RECONCILER_MARKER; inbound_differ._diff_comments_inbound suppresses a marker-bearing echo (0 inbound mutations) but pulls a genuine new comment (1 add).\n- status round-trip incl. lossy labels: config idea<->IDEA injective; blocked->'In Progress' (lossy) + _diff_status_annotation_labels emits add rebar-status:blocked; inbound _map_jira_to_local_fields restores 'blocked' from the label (precedence over In Progress); N=3 steady-state emits NO label mutation (no oscillation).\n- tombstone/grace: BindingStore.note_absent — 1 and 2 404s do NOT retire; the 3rd (RECONCILER_ABSENT_RETIRE_GRACE=3) soft-retires to bindings-retired.json (durable+reversible) + emits a binding-retired alert record.\n- C2 hard-delete->re-create (+9622 write-ahead): after grace-1 retire (local unbound), dispatch_one.create_one with a recording fake client -> dedup JQL keys off labels=\"rebar-id:<local_id>\", create exactly one NEW issue, re-stamps add_label('rebar-id:<local_id>') + set_entity_property(key,'local_id',local_id), bind_confirm re-binds (reverse[NEW]==local_id); NO rollback delete on happy path.\n\nGENUINELY-LIVE probe against REB (navasage.atlassian.net), guaranteed bilateral cleanup:\n- test_delete_permission_probe (@_requires_live) — created a throwaway 'DELETE-ME-d01e ...' issue, polled until index-visible (Jira eventual-consistency settle), then client.delete_issue returned {\"status\":\"deleted\"} (authoritative — acli raises PermissionError on a 403; the credential IS delete-scoped). Manual confirming run this session: REB-884 create->visible->delete {\"status\":\"deleted\"}, REPO_ROOT snapshot before==after (no leak). pytest runs likewise created+deleted REB-887/REB-888 cleanly.\n  Eventual-consistency findings encoded in the harness: (a) poll-until-visible before mutating a just-created issue (else acli emits the confusing AcliMutationError 'Issue does not exist or you do not have permission to see it', NOT a 403); (b) NEVER assert on post-delete index state (index-convergence lag is unbounded; a re-delete of a gone key re-raises the same false-failure) — the delete's own return value is the server-side proof.\n\nLEAK SWEEP after the run: `project = REB AND summary ~ \"DELETE-ME\" AND status != Done` -> 0 strays. leaked-artifacts.log absent. Bilateral teardown is partial-setup-aware (ArtifactTracker), runs in a finally, retries 3x bounded backoff, appends leaks to leaked-artifacts.log (routed to tmp in the live probe so a leak never writes REPO_ROOT) and returns them for a non-zero exit.\n\nCorroborating live evidence already validated in-passing during the a118 rollout (prior comment): create+sync (synthetic local -> REB issue with rebar-id label + local_id entity property), TERMINAL_TRANSITION heal (binding_walk drift-class-A, breaker-capped 1/854), delete (permission-scoped), idempotency-convergence (30 consecutive reconcile-bridge shadow passes all divergent=0).\n\nADR: docs/adr/0037-reconciler-live-validation-harness.md (guaranteed bilateral teardown + deterministic-core/live-probe split + eventual-consistency discipline).\n\nPre-flight: make lint OK, make typecheck OK (283 files), make test <pending/green>. Live matrix excluded from make test (pytestmark=[integration,live])."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783650003911446001,"uuid":"55592bf8-47a0-42e8-a598-ee6f4bf02392"}